## Summary
Fixes #7258 (partial). This patch adds support for `.size` on dynamic arrays and queues inside inline `randomize() with {}` constraints. Previously, `.size` in inline constraints triggered a `CONSTRAINTIGN` warning and was silently ignored, while the same construct worked correctly in class-level constraints.

## Reproducer
```systemverilog
class Packet;
  rand int unsigned m_length;
  rand byte m_data[];
  constraint c_length { m_length inside {[1:16]}; }
endclass

module t;
  initial begin
    Packet pkt = new;
    // .size in inline constraint -- worked in class constraints, failed here
    int ok = pkt.randomize() with {
      m_data.size == m_length;
    };
  end
endmodule
```

On master:
```
%Warning-CONSTRAINTIGN: Unsupported: randomizing this expression, treating as state
    ... m_data.size == m_length;
              ^~~~
```
The `.size` constraint is silently dropped, so the array is not resized and the constraint is not enforced.

## Changes
- `src/V3Randomize.cpp`: Added pre-scan of the captured `with {}` expression tree for `DYN_SIZE`/`ASSOC_SIZE` method calls before passing to `ConstraintExprVisitor`. For each `.size` call on a rand dynamic/queue array, creates a size variable (reusing `createOrGetSizeVar` helper), replaces the `.size` node with a VarRef to the size variable, appends a `size >= 0` constraint, and generates a post-solve resize statement guarded by solver success.
- `src/V3Randomize.cpp`: Extracted `createOrGetSizeVar` and `createSizeGteZeroConstraint` as shared helpers, deduplicating the existing class-level constraint path.
- `test_regress/t/t_randomize_method_types_unsup.out`: Updated golden output -- `.size` in inline constraints no longer produces `CONSTRAINTIGN`.

## Test
- Added `test_regress/t/t_constraint_dyn_size_inline.{v,py}` -- tests inline `.size` constraints with multiple dynamic arrays, cross-field size binding, and `foreach` element constraints.

